abstract: The classification of the giant planet magnetospheres into two varieties is examined: the large symmetric magnetospheres of Jupiter and Saturn and the smaller irregular ones of Uranus and Neptune. The characteristics of the plasma and the current understanding of the magnetospheric processes are considered for each planet. The energetic particle populations, radio emissions, and remote sensing of magnetospheric processes in the giant planet magneotospheres are discussed.
title: Giant planet magnetospheres

publications.publicationName: In: Annual review of earth and planetary sciences. Vol. 20 (A93-45370 18-46)
